				<width>1256</width>
				<height>700</height>
				<font>font16_textbox</font>
				<textcolor>grey2</textcolor>
				<pagecontrol>62</pagecontrol>
				<label>[B]This skin is based on Silvo's mod and further modded by DW. [/B][CR][CR][B]Handy Hotkeys[/B][CR]   • x - [I]stop playback[/I][CR]   • m - [I]media menu buttons during playback[/I][CR]   • spacebar - [I]pause playback[/I][CR]   • backspace - [I]previous screen[/I][CR]   • c - [I]context menu[/I][CR]   • two dots at top of list - [I]back to previous list[/I][CR]   • i - [I]basic media info during playback[/I][CR]   • o - [I]detailed media info during playback[/I][CR][CR][B]Background Images[/B][CR]   • [I]Background images are located in the userdata\backgrounds folder if you want to add your own.[/I][CR]   • [I]Change backgrounds by selecting 'single image' > _backgrounds > userdata > backgrounds in the menu customizer.[/I][CR][CR][CR][B]How do I keep the Music information on the screen permanently?[/B][CR]   • [I]The info button toggles how music information is displayed. When it disappears press info to re-show it and never press it a second time to hide it. If it is hidden then it will display for 10 seconds after a song is played or the next track in your queue begins.[/I][CR][CR][B]How do I customize this skin?[/B][CR]   • [I]To customize the Main Menu navigate to System > Interface > Configure skin to access the skin wide settings and main menu customization. Select [/I][B] Set up the Aeon Nox main menu[/B] [I]where you can enable/disable any item, customize what happens when you select that item, set up backgrounds, widgets, manage the submenu, and choose a custom label.[/I][CR][CR]   • [I]There are more options located in Skin settings > Customization for things like the OSD (On Screen Display) for fullscreen music and video playback, skin color picker, and the video information dialog.[/I][CR][CR]   • [I]There are also many settings for each viewtype and/or section (Music, Movie, TV Show) in the side menu so play around with all the options for further customization.[/I]</label>
				<visible>!String.IsEmpty(Window(skinsettings).Property(FAQ))</visible>
			</control>
